  "datePublished": "2026-03-08",
  "description": "TOPS (tera operations per second, or trillion operations per second) is a throughput metric for hardware accelerators, measuring how many integer operations (typically INT8 multiply-accumulate) the processor can perform per second. It is the standard metric for comparing NPU capabilities.\nMicrosoft\u0026rsquo;s Copilot+ PC specification requires 40 TOPS minimum. The Qualcomm Snapdragon X Elite delivers 45 TOPS; its successor, the Snapdragon X2 Elite, delivers 80 TOPS. Apple\u0026rsquo;s M4 NPU delivers approximately 38 TOPS.\n",
  "name": "TOPS",
